In this release, data for beta-glucan in mushrooms, except Agaricus bisporus (white button, crimini, portabella) have been replaced with results from analysis using the updated protocol which has trehalase enzyme added to the protocol, addressing potential overestimation of Î²-glucan content in samples containing trehalose (K-YBGL, 08/23. Previously K-YBGL, 11/19). Values for Agaricus mushrooms were not updated due to low levels of beta-glucan and no difference beyond analytical uncertainty resulting from the modified procedure.
